item.description:
arXiv:2501.08519v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: In this work, we investigate the semileptonic decays of $B_{(s)}$ meson to $D_{0}^{\ast}(2300)$, $D_{s0}^{\ast}(2317)$, $D_{s1}(2460)$, $D_{s1}(2536)$, $D_{1}(2420)$ and $D_{1}(2430)$ in the covariant light-front quark model (CLFQM). We combine the helicity amplitudes via the corresponding form factors to obtain the branching ratios of the semileptonic decays $B_{(s)} 	o D^{**}_{(s)}\ell 
u_\ell$ with $D^{**}_{(s)}$ referring to a P-wave exicted charmed meson $D_{0}^{\ast}(2300)$, $D_{s0}^{\ast}(2317)$, $D_{s1}(2460)$, $D_{s1}(2536)$, $D_{1}(2420)$ or $D_{1}(2430)$ and $\ell=e, \mu, 	au$. Furthermore, we also take into account another two physical observables, namely the longitudinal polarization fraction $f_L$ and the forward-backward asymmetry $A_{FB}$. Most of our predictions are comparable to the results given by other theoretical approaches and the present available data. The branching ratios of the semileptonic decay channels $B_{s} 	o D_{s1}(2460) \ell 
u_\ell$ and $B 	o D_{1}(2420) \ell 
u_\ell$ are larger than those of the semileptonic decays $B_{s} 	o D_{s1}(2536) \ell 
u_\ell$ and $B 	o D_{1}(2430) \ell 
u_\ell$, respectively. We find that the long-standing '$1/2$ vs $3/2$ puzzle' in the decays $B^{+}	o  ar{D}_1^{(\prime)0} \ell^{\prime+}
u_{\ell^\prime}$ $(\ell^\prime=e,\mu)$ can be solved by taking some negative mixing angle $	heta_s$ values within a range from $-30.3^\circ$ to $-24.9^\circ$, corresponding to $	heta$ of about $5^\circ\sim10.4^\circ$. While Belle collaboration updated their measurements for the decays $B^{0}	o D^{*-}_0 \ell^{\prime+}
u_{\ell^\prime}$ with only a small upper limit $Br(B^{0}	o D^{*-}_0 \ell^{\prime+}
u_{\ell^\prime})<0.44	imes10^{-3}$ obtained, which is much larger than most theoretical predictions and causes a new puzzle.

item.title:
New physics searches via angular distributions of $  ar{B} 	o D^* (	o D \pi) 	au (	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell)  ar{
u}_	au$ decays

item.description:
arXiv:2411.09414v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: The study of $ ar{B} 	o D^* 	au { ar{
u}}_	au$ angular distribution can be used to obtain information about new physics (or beyond the Standard Model) couplings, which are motivated by various $B$ anomalies. However, the inability to measure precisely the three-momentum of the $	au$ lepton hinders such measurements, as the tau decay contains one or more undetected neutrinos. Here, we present a measurable angular distribution of $ ar{B} 	o D^* 	au { ar{
u}}_	au$ by considering the additional decay $	au 	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell$, where $\ell \in \{ e , \mu \}$. The full process used is $ ar{B} 	o D^* (	o D \pi) 	au (	o \ell 
u_	au  ar{
u}_\ell)  ar{
u}_	au$, in which only the $\ell$ and $D^*$ are reconstructed. A fit to the experimental angular distribution of this process can be used to extract information on new physics parameters. To demonstrate the feasibility of this approach, we generate simulated data for this process and perform a sensitivity study to obtain the expected statistical errors on new physics parameters from experiments in the near future. We obtain a sensitivity of the order of 5% for the right-handed current and around 6% for the tensor current. In addition, we use the recent lattice QCD data on $B 	o D^*$ form factors and obtain correlations between form factors and new physics parameters.
